                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d199">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Uhl</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Denby</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-05-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 17, 1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1069.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your No.
                    2182, of March 28 last, in relation to the refusal of the Russian Government to
                    grant permission for an American missionary to pass through Siberia en route to
                    the United States, and to the position assumed by that Government that temporary
                    refuge in Russian territory would not be accorded to Americans who might be
                    impelled to seek such refuge by threatened danger to their lives.</p>
                <p>The United States minister at St. Petersburg has been furnished with a copy of
                    your dispatch, and he has been instructed to take occasion to inquire whether
                    the Russian regulations against the residence or travel of foreign ecclesiastics
                    or missionaries in Siberia are as strict as Count Cassini interprets them to be,
                    even to the inhospitable degree of denying shelter to citizens of a friendly
                    State whose lives might be imperiled.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwin F. Uhl</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
